media:group.media:title: Category Theory - Lecture 7 Part 1
media:group.media:description: In this video we see that a category is (co)complete if it has all finite (co)products and (co)equalisers. Next we see a proof that right adjoints preserve limits. We see the definition of a monoidal category and some adjectives we can we can apply to them. We also see a bunch of examples.
